The course provides versatile and in-depth knowledge about the international entrepreneurship and innovation economics.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to create opportunities for acquiring the in-depth body of knowledge about international entrepreneurship and innovation as well as about relevant analytical tools and methods.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student who pass the course:  a) knows the key concepts within international entrepreneurship,  innovation economics and innovation management; b) understands the theoretical and practical questions of entrepreneurship and innovation of a company, from the co-operational, employee and manager perspectives; c) knows how to relate entrepreneurship and innovation with other fields of business administration and economics; d) can evaluate which factors and how affect innovation process of a firm; e) understands  the effects of innovation at the firm and at the aggregate economy level; f) knows how to apply main methods of business analysis; has an overview of the main methods applied in the empirical research of the determinants and effects of innovation; g) has acquired skills and experiences for the analysis of holistic functioning of entrepreneurial and innovation processes; h) has obtained positive attitudes towards acceptance of versatile and novel perspectives in entrepreneurial activities; i) is familiar with innovation problems in Estonian organizations and in a global context.
